cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.PL

The paper discusses the security of industrial control systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed system involves detecting changes in software behavior, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of electromagnetic side-channel measurements is a form of hardware security (cs.CY). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of Siemens S7-317 PLCs, which is a type of programmable logic controller (PL), further supporting the inclusion of cs.PL as a likely sub-category.
